    "background": "Consider the experiment of tossing fair coins. Define the following event: A : [Observing at least one head].",
    "data": null,
    "question": "Find P(A) if 2 coins are tossed."
  },
  "output": {
    "answer": "When 2 coins are tossed, we know that the event A : [Observe at least one head.] consists of the sample points A: {HH, HT, TH}. The complement of A is defined as the event that occurs when A does not occur. Therefore, A^c: {Observe no heads.} = {TT}. Since the coins are balanced, we have P(A^c) = P(TT) = 1/4 and P(A) = 1 - P(A^C) = 1 - 1/4 = 3/4."
  },
